<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-10-18T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-10-18T06:00:00-05:00" n="220" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d220">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.C001/833: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Poland</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Cudahy</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Warsaw</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-10-18T12:00:00+01:00">October
                                    18, 1933—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 12:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>57. Department’s circular telegram October 14, 10 a.m. Attitude of Polish
                            Government undisturbed awaiting expected developments prior to German
                            election. No action by Poland indicated. The press indicates no great
                            emotion, enjoins restraint awaiting events following Germany’s decision.
                            Count Szembek, Acting Minister of Foreign Affairs, informed me that he
                            had conferred with Pilsudski<note n="2" xml:id="d220fn2">Minister of
                                Military Affairs.</note> and Prime Minister<note n="3" xml:id="d220fn3">Col. Alexander Prystor.</note> and that no action
                            is contemplated pending developments. Foreign Minister expected from
                            Geneva 20th, after interviewing him will report to the Department.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Cudahy</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>